{{nihongo|'''Junnosuke Suzuki'''|鈴木 淳之介|Suzuki Junnosuke|born 12 July 2003}} is a Japanese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[F.C. Copenhagen|Copenhagen]] and the [[Japan national football team|Japan national team]].

==Club career==
===High school football===
After a year disrupted by the [[COVID-19 pandemic in Japan]], Suzuki represented the Teikyo University Kani High School at the [[2020 All Japan High School Soccer Tournament]], where his performance in Teikyo's 2–0 win against Meitoku Gijuku helped his side to the Round-of-16 for the first time.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://hochi.news/articles/20210102-OHT1T50138.html?page=1|title=【高校サッカー】湘南内定の２年生ＭＦ鈴木淳之介の帝京大可児、チーム最高タイの１６強進出「注目されるプレッシャーを力に…」|trans-title=[High school soccer] Shonan-bound second-year midfielder Suzuki Junnosuke of Teikyo University Kani advances to the round of 16, tying the team's best record: "Turning the pressure of being in the spotlight into strength..."|date=2 January 2021|access-date=23 May 2025|website=hochi.news|language=ja}}</ref> The following year, he again impressed in helping Teikyo win the [[Gifu Prefecture]] National [[High school football|High School Football]] Championship, scoring the opening goal in the 6–1 win against Chukyo in the final.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chunichi.co.jp/article/365385|title=高校2年でプロ入り内定の逸材・帝京大可児の鈴木淳之介が勝利の立役者に【高校サッカー】|trans-title=Junnosuke Suzuki of Teikyo University Kani, a talented player who is set to go professional as a second-year high school student, is the key player in the victory [High school soccer]|date=13 November 2021|access-date=23 May 2025|website=chunichi.co.jp|language=ja}}</ref> At the [[2021 All Japan High School Soccer Tournament]] he provided two assists in Teikyo's 4–1 win against Imabari Higashi in the first round.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.chunichi.co.jp/article/392759|title=来季J1湘南内定の鈴木淳之介が2アシスト　帝京大可児が4発快勝で初戦突破【全国高校サッカー】|trans-title=Junnosuke Suzuki, who will play for Shonan in the J1 League next season, provided two assists as Teikyo University Kani won their first match with four goals [National High School Soccer]|date=29 December 2021|access-date=23 May 2025|website=chunichi.co.jp|language=ja}}</ref>

===Shonan Bellmare===
Having committed to sign for [[J1 League]] side [[Shonan Bellmare]] at the end of the 2020 season, Suzuki joined the club in 2022.<ref name=bunshun>{{cite web|url=https://number.bunshun.jp/articles/-/846520?page=1|title=＜選手権は1、2年生に注目？＞高2でJ1湘南内定・鈴木淳之介がライバル視する青森山田の10番とは|trans-title=<Will the championship be focused on first and second year students?> Junnosuke Suzuki, a second year high school student who has been accepted into the J1 Shonan Nankai League, sees Aomori Yamada's number 10 as his rival|date=30 December 2020|access-date=23 May 2025|website=number.bunshun.jp|language=ja}}</ref> He made his professional debut the same year, playing all ninety minutes in Shonan Bellmare's 3–0 win against [[Vertfee Yaita]] in the [[Emperor's Cup]] on 1 June 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bellmare.co.jp/288170|title=【馬入日記：6月3日】天皇杯でプロデビュー！鈴木淳之介選手インタビュー|trans-title=[Umairi Diary: June 3] Professional debut at Emperor's Cup! Interview with Junnosuke Suzuki|date=3 June 2022|access-date=23 May 2025|website=bellmare.co.jp|language=ja}}</ref>

Having struggled to secure a place in the first team, making only five league appearances in the 2023 season, a change of position from defensive midfield to central defence saw Suzuki's playing time improve.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soccerdigestweb.com/news/detail/id=154937|title=「伝えられたのは試合の２日前くらい」湘南MF鈴木淳之介がCBへのコンバートで才能開花なるか「出られるならどこでも良い」|trans-title="I was informed about it about two days before the match" Shonan midfielder Junnosuke Suzuki's talents may blossom as he is converted to CB, "I don't care where I play as long as I can play"|date=6 June 2024|access-date=23 May 2025|website=soccerdigestweb.com|language=ja}}</ref><ref name=us>{{cite web|url=https://web.ultra-soccer.jp/news/view?news_no=477602|title=J1湘南、プレータイム大幅増の21歳MF鈴木淳之介と契約更新「充実した一年になるように頑張ります!」|trans-title=J1 League Shonan renews contract with 21-year-old midfielder Suzuki Junnosuke, who has seen a significant increase in playing time: "I'll do my best to make this a fulfilling year!"|date=28 December 2024|access-date=23 May 2025|website=web.ultra-soccer.jp|language=ja}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bellmare.co.jp/357513|title=My Story|access-date=23 May 2025|website=bellmare.co.jp|language=ja}}</ref> Following a suspension after accumulating too many yellow cards, media in Japan cited Suzuki's absence for Shonan Bellmare's poor performance in a 1–1 draw with [[Avispa Fukuoka]] on 7 August 2024.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.soccerdigestweb.com/news/detail/id=158997|title=【湘南】鈴木淳之介不在の福岡戦で見えたビルドアップの弱点。左右のストッパーは替えが効かない|trans-title=[Shonan] The weakness of the build-up was revealed in the match against Fukuoka without Junnosuke Suzuki. The left and right stoppers are not replaceable|date=8 August 2024|access-date=23 May 2025|website=soccerdigestweb.com|language=ja}}</ref> He won the Young Player of the Month award for October 2024, having been credited with good performances, including in Shonan Bellmare's 2–1 win against [[Sanfrecce Hiroshima]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jleague.jp/monthly_awards/2024/10/youngplayer/j1.html|title=明治安田Ｊリーグ月間ヤングプレーヤー賞|trans-title=Meiji Yasuda J.League Young Player of the Month Award|access-date=23 May 2025|website=jleague.jp|language=ja}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kanaloco.jp/sports/soccer/bellmare/article-1125288.html|title=Ｊ１湘南　鈴木淳之介が初のヤングプレーヤー賞、山口監督も受賞|trans-title=J1 Shonan's Junnosuke Suzuki receives his first Young Player Award, manager Yamaguchi also receives the award|date=12 November 2024|access-date=23 May 2025|website=kanaloco.jp|language=ja}}</ref>

Suzuki renewed his contract with Shonan Bellmare at the conclusion of the 2024 season.<ref name=us/> Having featured mostly as a left centre-back in a back three for Shonan Bellmare, he showed adaptability when he was moved to the middle of the three for a game against [[Avispa Fukuoka]] in April 2025, helping Shonan Bellmare keep a [[Shutout|clean sheet]] in a 0–0 draw.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/news/202504290001465.html|title=【湘南】CBコンバートの鈴木淳之介、初３バックの中央でどんと構えて無失点「我慢強くやれた」|trans-title=[Shonan] Junnosuke Suzuki, converted to CB, stood tall in the center of his first three-back formation and kept the score at zero, saying, "I was patient."|date=29 April 2025|access-date=23 May 2025|website=nikkansports.com|language=ja}}</ref> His good form continued, and by May 2025, he led the J1 League in ariel duels won.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.infoseek.co.jp/article/footballzone_591068/|title=森保監督がJ視察で見つけた「楽しみな選手」　逸材21歳が外国人とのバトル「ほぼほぼ制していた」|trans-title="Exciting player" that Coach Moriyasu found during his J-League observation tour: 21-year-old talented player "almost dominated" the battle against foreign players|date=8 May 2025|access-date=23 May 2025|website=news.infoseek.co.jp|language=ja}}</ref>

===FC Copenhagen===
On 9 July 2025, [[Danish Superliga]] club [[F.C. Copenhagen]] announced the signing of Suzuki on a five-year deal.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fck.dk/nyhed/fc-koebenhavn-henter-japanske-junnosuke-suzuki|title=F.C. København henter japanske Junnosuke Suzuki|trans-title=F.C. Copenhagen signs Japanese Junnosuke Suzuki|publisher=FC Copenhagen|date=9 July 2025|access-date=24 July 2025|language=da}}</ref>

==International career==
Without having previously represented Japan at youth international level, he was called up to the [[Japan national football team|senior squad]] in May 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nikkansports.com/soccer/japan/news/202505230001763.html|title=【日本代表】初選出の21歳湘南DF鈴木淳之介「小さい頃からの夢だった」今季全試合で先発|trans-title=[Japan National Team] 21-year-old Shonan DF Junnosuke Suzuki was selected for the first time and has started in every game this season, saying, "It's been my dream since I was a child."|date=23 May 2025|access-date=23 May 2025|website=nikkansports.com|language=ja}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Initially a [[defensive midfielder]], he was noted during his high school years for his ability to read the game, as well as being able to play in both defensive and offensive capacities.<ref name=bunshun/> Suzuki has described himself as a good passer with good dribbling, citing [[Frenkie de Jong]] and [[Andrés Iniesta]] as players he liked to watch.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://yansaka.com/funny/post_004754.html|title=岐阜の強豪・帝京大可児高校サッカー部-エース・鈴木淳之介の誓い「プロの練習に行って一番違うなと思ったのは、守備の強度でした」【2021年 第100回全国高校サッカー選手権 出場校】|trans-title=Gifu's powerhouse, Teikyo University Kani High School Soccer Club - Ace Suzuki Junnosuke's pledge: "The biggest difference I noticed when I went to professional training was the strength of the defense" [Participating in the 100th All Japan High School Soccer Championship in 2021]|date=8 November 2021|access-date=23 May 2025|website=yansaka.com|language=ja}}</ref>

Following an injury to [[Kim Min-tae]], Suzuki was brought in to cover at centre-back for Shonan Bellmare's J1 League match against [[Gamba Osaka]] in June 2024.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.kanaloco.jp/sports/soccer/bellmare/article-1082604.html|title=Ｊ１湘南・鈴木淳之介がセンターバックで初先発「やってやろうと思った」|trans-title=J1 Shonan's Junnosuke Suzuki makes his first start as a center back: "I thought I'd give it a go"|date=1 June 2024|access-date=23 May 2025|website=kanaloco.jp|language=ja}}</ref> The change of position was beneficial for Suzuki, as in April 2025 he was named as the best centre-back under 25 years old in the J1 League by the [[International Centre for Sports Studies]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://web.gekisaka.jp/news/jleague/detail/?427120-427120-fl|title=欧州の調査機関がJ1若手CBでトップ評価…昨季コンバートで急台頭の湘南21歳DF鈴木淳之介「やり続けるだけ」|trans-title=European research institute rates J1 top young CB... Shonan 21-year-old defender Suzuki Junnosuke, who rose to prominence after being converted last season, "just keeps doing it"|date=3 April 2025|access-date=23 May 2025|website=web.gekisaka.jp|language=ja}}</ref>

